33
00:01:41,935 --> 00:01:46,838
Design events, not APIs: Think about what happened, not what to do.

34
00:01:46,838 --> 00:01:51,742
Use schemas: Avro or Protobuf for type safety and evolution.

35
00:01:51,742 --> 00:01:56,177
Partition wisely: Choose partition keys that ensure ordering where needed.

36
00:01:56,177 --> 00:02:00,781
Handle failures: Implement DLQs and retry mechanisms.

37
00:02:00,781 --> 00:02:05,108
Monitor everything: Consumer lag is your early warning system.

38
